- At T $=0 \mathrm{~K}$, silicon is an insulator; no charge flows through it.
- When silicon atoms come together to form a crystal, the electrons occupy particular allowed energy bands.
- At T $=0 \mathrm{~K}$, all valence electrons occupy the valence energy band
