$$V_{C C}=v_{C E}+i_{C} R_{C}$$
- The base current is established by $V_{B B}$ and $R_{B}$, and the resulting collector current is $i_{C}=\beta i_{B}$.
- If we set $V_{B B}=0$, the $\mathrm{B}-\mathrm{E}$ junction will have zero applied volts; therefore, $i_{B}=0$, which implies that $i_{C}=0$. This condition is called cutoff.

\section*{Current Relationships}
$$i_{E}=i_{B}+i_{C}$$
$$i_{C}=\beta i_{B}$$
(Forward Active Mode)
$i_{E}$ Can therefore be written as:
$$\begin{aligned}
